The paper proposes a method for sparsification of deep neural networks, which is a common topic in the machine learning community. The paper specifically focuses on making the sparsification process fully differentiable, which is relevant to the sub-category of "cs.LG" (Machine Learning). The method is also applicable to various popular models, which suggests relevance to sub-categories such as "cs.NE" (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), "cs.CV" (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), "cs.AI" (Artificial Intelligence), and "cs.CL" (Computation and Language).
